Robert Joseph Taylor (1 November 1873 in Liverpool – ?) was an English first-class cricketer, who played in three matches, two for Lancashire in June 1898 and one for Worcestershire in August 1900. He also played for Lancashire Second XI between 1897 and 1899.
Taylor took two first-class wickets, both for Lancashire: his victims were Frederick Holland and Gregor MacGregor.
